dcterms:creator: Alex Krizhevsky
dcterms:description: A dataset containing 60,000 32x32 color images in 10 classes, with 6,000 images per class. The dataset is commonly used for training machine learning models in image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-10

dcterms:creator: Alex Krizhevsky
dcterms:description: A dataset containing 60,000 32x32 color images in 100 classes, with 600 images per class. It is used for more fine-grained image classification tasks compared to CIFAR-10.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-100

dcterms:description: A large-scale hierarchical image database containing over 14 million images, organized according to the WordNet hierarchy. It is widely used for training and benchmarking image classification models.
dcterms:title: ImageNet
